    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>You become a conduit for all possible realities and timelines, enabling you to twist events with little warning. As a reaction, you can reduce the spell’s remaining duration by 1 round to produce one of the following effects.</p>\n<p><strong>•</strong> Use your Will save bonus in place of your Fortitude or Reflex bonus for one saving throw.</p>\n<p><strong>•</strong> Use your Reflex save bonus in place of your Fortitude or Will bonus for one saving throw.</p>\n<p><strong>•</strong> After seeing the roll but before learning the result of one attack roll, ability check, skill check, or saving throw made by you or an ally within 30 feet, you can roll 1d20 + your caster level + your spellcasting ability score modifier and apply its result in place of the triggering attack roll, save, or check.</p>\n<p><strong>•</strong> You can attempt to deflect an attack that would otherwise hit you. Roll 1d20 + your caster level + your spellcasting ability score modifier and compare the result to the attack roll. If your result equals or exceeds the attack roll’s result, treat the attack as a miss.</p>"
